body:
I did hope but it's not. When deadlock occuring, `PDO::inTransaction()` is still `true`.

What about such patch? It keep throwing original exception from transaction body, ignoring (logging) exception from `rollback()`.

```diff
 } catch (\Exception $e) {
     if ($transaction->isActive && $transaction->level === $level) {
+        try {
             $transaction->rollBack();
+        } catch (\Exception $e_rollback) {
+            \Yii::error($e_rollback, __METHOD__);
+            // continue to throw original exception $e
+        }
     }
     throw $e;
 }
```

Both exception has previous exception, so it cannot be attached to each other without separate exception class.

Is PR acceptable? Is test case required (can second connection be opened just with `DatabaseTestCase::prepareDatabase()` keeping other tests work?)?
